.TH "spi_test_run_test" 9 "spi_test_run_test" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_test_run_test \- run an individual spi_test including all the relevant iterations on: length and buffer alignment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spi_test_run_test
.BI "(struct spi_device *spi "  ","
.BI "const struct spi_test *test "  ","
.BI "void *tx "  ","
.BI "void *rx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "spi" 12
the spi_device to send the messages to
.IP "test" 12
the test which we need to execute
.IP "tx" 12
the tx buffer allocated for the test sequence
.IP "rx" 12
the rx buffer allocated for the test sequence
.SH "RETURN"
status code of spi_sync or other failures
